audio_descriptions.notes:
The video begins with three cover slides

The first reads: Inspired thinking brought to you by Resource

The second has a circle logo on the left with the words "out there", the slide reads TEDX Columbus, x=independently organized TED event

final slide reads: Michelle Alexander. Lawyer, Advocate, Scholar

The video then opens to Michelle Alexander, a middle aged black woman on stage in a large auditorium. The stage is decorated with white circles connected with black lines and a sign reads Tedx Columbus. During the video the camera perspective will shift between a view of the stage and a view of the audience. There are no visual aids utilized during the presentation other than subtle emphasis given through non-verbals. All non-verbal queues are consistent with presenter audio.

result.title: The future of race in America: Michelle Alexander at TEDxColumbus
result.description: In the spirit of ideas worth spreading, TEDx is a program of local, self-organized events that bring people together to share a TED-like experience. At a TEDx event, TEDTalks video and live speakers combine to spark deep discussion and connection in a small group. These local, self-organized events are branded TEDx, where x = independently organized TED event. The TED Conference provides general guidance for the TEDx program, but individual TEDx events are self-organized.* (*Subject to certain rules and regulations)
